				 Murder scan on servant
 A STAFF REPORTERA 66-year-old woman was found dead at her home on Shyampukur Street on Tuesday morning.																								Sabita Bandopadhyays body																								 was recovered from her bedroom with blood oozing from																								 her nose. Habu, her servant, was found in the bathroom,																								 his hands and legs tied and mouth gagged with a tape.																								 Jewellery worth a few lakhs were missing from an almirah																							 in the room.																								Habu, who slept on the floor in Sabitas first-floor room on Monday night, has been detained for questioning. It seems the elderly woman was choked to death with a pillow, said the deputy commissioner of police (north), Damayanti Sen.																								Around 6am, a tenant on the ground floor told me that he could hear Habus muffled cries from the first floor. I went upstairs and found the door of my mothers room open. My mother was lying on the bed, blood oozing from her nose, while Habu was tied up in the bathroom, said Anindita Nag Chowdhury, Sabitas daughter. who had come to the Shyampukur Street house a day before.																								We did not hear any sound last night. We suspect Habu is the culprit, alleged Anindita. Neither of Sabitas two sons was in the house on Monday.
